The design presents a clear overview of digital literacy, including its definition, useful digital tools for students, and safe internet practices. 
It highlights how digital literacy involves using technology responsibly, improving productivity through tools like Google Docs and Canva, and maintaining online safety through strong passwords, privacy settings, and awareness of cyber threats.
The visual layout combines text and graphics to make the information easy to understand and engaging. 
The circular diagram on the right represents different aspects of digital literacy such as creativity, communication, collaboration, and e-safety, giving a holistic view of the concept.
One interesting aspect while creating this infographic was exploring different design elements and organizing information in a visually appealing way. 
However, I found it slightly difficult to balance text and visuals without making the design look crowded. Overall, this task helped me understand both digital literacy concepts and basic design skills.
